63
Some of those speculations
formed upon insulated facts
brings to my mind
a narration, an
ingenious person had
made a system of
[underline]Geology[/underline], in which He
attempted to shew that
all rocks & soils
were the produce of
alluvions.- - & He founded
his reasoning upon the facts
of the Gravel pits of Kensington
where only he had studied
geology - .

